title: S.J. football: Welsh springs Shawnee past rival Cherokee
text:
Shawnee is ranked No. 15 in South Jersey by The Inquirer.
Powell finished with one touchdown pass for No. 4 Cherokee. 
WEST JERSEY AMERICAN 
Williamstown 52, Eastern 7: Rich Stanzione and Tyrik Glenn ran for two scores each to lead the the host No. 6 Braves. 
WEST JERSEY CONSTITUTION 
Paul VI 62, Triton 14: Lonnie Moore returned the opening kick 74 yards to the endzone and the host 11th-ranked Eagles rolled from there. 
WEST JERSEY CLASSIC 
Gloucester 20, Clayton 6: Vincent DiGiacomo ran 19 times for 115 yards and a touchdown to lead the home team. He also caught a touchdown. 
WEST JERSEY LIBERTY 
Haddonfield 45, Audubon 0: Tommy Kadar completed 9 of 15 passes for 253 yards and five touchdowns to power No. 13 Bulldawgs at home. Kadar also ran for 60 yards and grabbed an interception. Matt Burns made three catches for 99 yards and two touchdowns. Jake Curran made 12 tackles. 
Holy Cross 21, Bordentown 18: Tim Petrucelli picked off a pass in the end zone in the first quarter and then ran in a 50-yard touchdown in the second quarter to give the hosts the lead for good. Petrucelli finished with 206 yards on 27 carries. 
WEST JERSEY ROYAL 
Camden Catholic 48, Highland 20: Marcus Hillman and Tyree Rodgers scored defensive touchdowns in the first quarter to get things started for the No. 5 Irish at home. 
Woodrow Wilson 36, Cumberland 0: Aran Lee threw for two touchdowns and ran for another to lead the No. 22 Tigers on the road. 
Camden 33 Bishop Eustace 10: Brad Hawkins caught a touchdown pass and also returned a fumble for a TD to lead the visiting No. 9 Panthers. 
CAPE-ATLANTIC AMERICAN 
St. Augustine 56, Egg Harbor Township 0: Kyle Dobbins piled up 185 yards and three touchdowns on 17 carries to lead the No. 2 Hermits on the road. Dobbins, who has 1,161 yards this season, became the sixth 1,000-yard rusher in program history. The sophomore received an offer from Temple earlier this week. 
NONLEAGUE
